  • Classes in com.jnape.palatable.lambda.lens used by com.jnape.palatable.lambda.adt.hmap 
    Class and Description
    Iso
    An Iso (short for "isomorphism") is an invertible Lens: a LensLike encoding of a bi-directional focusing of two types, and like Lenses, can be Viewed, Set, and Overed.
    Iso.Simple
    A convenience type with a simplified type signature for common isos with both unified "larger" values and unified "smaller" values.
    Lens
    An approximation of van Laarhoven lenses.
    Lens.Simple
    A convenience type with a simplified type signature for common lenses with both unified "larger" values and unified "smaller" values.
    LensLike
    The generic supertype of all types that can be treated as lenses but should preserve type-specific return types in overrides.
    LensLike.Simple
    A simpler type signature for lenses where S/T and A/B are equivalent.
